  "text": "The major kubelet components in kubernetes/kubernetes owned by sig-node are: (1) Pod Lifecycle Manager implemented in pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go, which defines the PodWorkers interface and podWorkers struct that manages the lifecycle of pods through synchronous and asynchronous operations. (2) Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client implemented in pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go, which defines the kubeGenericRuntimeManager struct that acts as the bridge between kubelet and container runtimes via the CRI API. (3) Volume Manager implemented in pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/volume_manager.go, which provides the VolumeManager interface for managing attachment, mounting, and unmounting of volumes to pods. (4) Device Plugin Manager implemented in pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/plugin_manager.go, which implements the PluginManager interface for managing the registration and deregistration of device plugins. All of these components are core parts of the kubelet architecture as defined in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository and are part of sig-node's responsibility for node-level functionality."
}

